        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 5:57PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Deerfield, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Holcomb and Deerfield around 600 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
